imshow(edge_image, []);
```

In this modified code, we first filter the grayscale image `gray_image` using the `imgaussfilt` function with a standard deviation of 2 to reduce noise in the image. Then, we proceed with applying the Sobel operators in the x and y directions as before and compute the edge image. Finally, we display the resulting edge image using `imshow`.

You can adjust the standard deviation parameter of the Gaussian filter (`sigma = 2` in this example) to control the amount of smoothing applied to the image before edge detection. Feel free to experiment with different values to achieve the desired edge detection results.

