Here is a JavaScript function that takes a sentence as input and switches the order of adjectives in the sentence:

```javascript
function switchAdjectiveOrder(sentence) {
  // Split the sentence into an array of words
  let words = sentence.split(" ");

  // Loop through the words to find adjectives and their positions
  for (let i = 0; i < words.length - 1; i++) {
    if (words[i + 1] === "beautiful" || words[i + 1] === "green" || words[i + 1] === "tall" || words[i + 1] === "big") {
      // Swap the positions of the current word and the next word
      let temp = words[i];
      words[i] = words[i + 1];
      words[i + 1] = temp;
      i++; // Skip the next word since it has already been processed
    }
  }

  // Join the words back together to form the modified sentence
  let modifiedSentence = words.join(" ");

  return modifiedSentence;
}

// Example usage
let originalSentence = "Beautiful green trees are in the park";
let modifiedSentence = switchAdjectiveOrder(originalSentence);
console.log(modifiedSentence); // Output: "Green beautiful trees are in the park"
```

In this function, we split the input sentence into an array of words. Then, we loop through the words and find the adjectives ("beautiful", "green", "tall", "big") and their positions. For each adjective found, we swap its position with the next word to switch the order of adjectives. Finally, we join the words back together to form the modified sentence.

